John,<br><br>
I appreciate your last post. Thanks for the insight of your diaries. I would be interested in reading more.<br><br>
I agree when you say that none of us has this figured out. I find that many times my own viewpoints are simplistic. <br><br>
The VC/NVA using political agitation is not surprising. However, the perception was made believable because of the history of the French in Vietnam. <br><br>
Concerning your reference to &quot;dog eat dog, dog kill dog&quot;, I was browsing Karnow's _History Of Vietnam_, trying to cross reference things I have mentioned from Neil Sheehan's book _A Bright Shining Lie_. In his book, Sheehan talks of Diem's Communist Denunciation Campaign where former Viet Minh and relatives -even non communists who fought the French - were hunted down and executed without any type of due process. Karnow mentions much of what Sheehan was saying about the campaign, plus he talks of a &quot;mirror image&quot; occurring. At the same time, in the north, communist cadres were whipping the peasants into a frenzy. Landlords were being executed by the thousands. Terror was perpetrated by *both sides* in the north and in the south. Due process of law was absent under *both regimes*.<br><br>
To paraphrase Karnow about Geneva in 1954, he says that the Viet Minh gave up, at Geneva, everything they had won on the battlefield. <br><br>
There were supposed to be elections in 1956. Diem refused to consent to the referendum (which Eisenhower predicted Ho Chi Minh would win). About the elections: the Americans stated that the matter &quot;should be left up to the Vietnamese&quot;. I find that incredible!<br><br>
The &quot;stay behinds&quot; in the south had been instructed to agitate politically - not to openly oppose, by force, the Diem regime. <br><br>
In the 1950's, the northern Communists had the priority of rebuilding the north - where most of the fighting with the French had taken place. They could not afford to wage a war in the south at that time. They figured that the elections would give them control of the country anyway. It would be self defeating for them to wage violence against Diem.<br><br>
Terror was used by both sides.<br><br>

